[DhtmlXQ_comment0]sg 20121022 1983 DunHuang Cup Liu DaHua W Liang WenBin D05 ||||ECCO:D05 ?????????||ECCO D05 Same Direction Cannons: Ranked Chariot vs File chariot with riverbank chariot variation.||||Jim: This game was played back in 1983. It is a short but very exciting game. Playing red was GM Liu DaHua while black was Master Liang WenBing, who is well known as the Gold Medal Coach in China.||Both were in their heyday when this game was played: GM Liu having won the National Championships in 1980-1981, while Master Liang came in 3rd place in his first apperance in the same competion in 1977 and has obtained good results over the next few years.||This game was published in a recent edition of "Xiangqi" but unfortunately, the commentator was unknown. ||Master Huang ShaoLong had commented on this game also. Very nice variations were given by him.||The comments given without any name would belong to the magazine's. ||PS: Master Huang and Mastera Liang both tied for 3rd place in the 1977 CNSC...[/DhtmlXQ_comment0]
